# English-Only Content Rule

All text that the end user can see in the ARO website must be written in **English**.
This applies to every page, section, component, marketing copy, microcopy, CTAs,
tooltips, labels, alt text, metadata (title, meta description, Open Graph),
error messages, footer links, and any new feature added in the future.

## Scope

- `index.html` (all pages: `#page-home`, `#page-floss`, `#page-pick`, `#page-flow`,
  `#page-ez`, `#page-fuel`, and any future page).
- Any new HTML file, template, or component added to the project.
- SVG illustrations with inline `<text>` elements.
- `alt`, `aria-label`, `title`, `placeholder` attributes.

## Rules

- Never introduce Spanish (or any non-English) copy into user-visible text.
- Product names stay in their canonical form: `ARO-FLOSS`, `ARO-PIK`, `ARO-FLO`,
  `ARO-EZ`, `ARO-FUEL`.
- If the user requests a change in Spanish, translate the intent and implement
  the final copy in English.
- Code comments and commit messages may be in any language; only user-facing
  content is restricted.

## Examples

```html
<!-- BAD -->
<h2>NUESTROS PRODUCTOS</h2>
<p>La forma más inteligente de tomar tus vitaminas.</p>
<button>Comprar ahora</button>

<!-- GOOD -->
<h2>OUR PRODUCTS</h2>
<p>The smarter way to take your vitamins.</p>
<button>Shop Now</button>
```

```html
<!-- BAD -->
<img src="aro_floss.png" alt="Hilo dental con vitaminas" />

<!-- GOOD -->
<img src="aro_floss.png" alt="Vitamin-coated floss pick" />
```
